    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "WHY CLIPBOARD EXISTS:\n\nWe exist to lift as many people up the socioeconomic ladder as possible. We dramatically improve lives by letting professionals turn extra time and ambition into career growth and financial opportunity. We achieve this with our app-based marketplace that connects workplaces and professionals, allowing professionals to book on-demand shifts and workplaces to access on-demand talent.\n\n\nABOUT CLIPBOARD:\n\nClipboard is a fast-growing Series C marketplace. We are a leader in our Long Term Care vertical and are expanding into several others (Dental, Home Health, etc.), as well as building out a full-time product.\nWe are a YC Top Company https://www.ycombinator.com/topcompanies/ with a global, remote team of 1,000+ people. We have been profitable since 2022, and fill millions of shifts annually at partner workplaces across the U.S., where tens of thousands of professionals work with us every year.\nWe are looking for your help to keep growing so we can serve more professionals and workplaces.\n\nTo learn more about us, take a look at our website here https://www.clipboardhealth.com/careers.\n\nOur Platform Engineers\n\n - Design, build, and maintain scalable infrastructure using Terraform, ensuring reproducibility, security, and automation across environments.\n\n - Develop and support backend services using TypeScript, NestJS, and Node.js, interfacing with MongoDB and Postgres databases to ensure performance and reliability.\n\n - Manage and optimize our cloud infrastructure on AWS, leveraging services like EC2, ECS, RDS, S3, CloudWatch, and more to support application and platform needs.\n\n - Build reusable infrastructure modules and internal tooling to empower product engineering teams and improve development velocity.\n\n - Own the full lifecycle of platform features: from design and implementation to monitoring and supporting them in production.\n\n - Work in a globally distributed, 100% remote team with asynchronous workflows and high ownership culture.\n   \n\nYou Might Be a Good Fit If\n\n - You’ve worked in high-growth startup environments or similarly fast-paced, agile teams—and possibly launched something on your own.\n\n - You have hands-on experience managing cloud infrastructure, CI/CD pipelines, and production systems, with a strong DevOps mindset.\n\n - You’ve built and supported web and backend systems using modern cloud-native tools and frameworks.\n\n - You’re excited by infrastructure as code, automation, and driving platform-level improvements that support other engineering teams.\n\n - You enjoy working deeply on technical systems but also communicate clearly and proactively with the team.\n\n - Talking to users or teammates to understand pain points and drive solutions energizes you.\n   \n\nPerks of Working with Us\n\n - Do meaningful work in healthcare—supporting real users whose lives are improved by your contributions.\n\n - Build platform capabilities that directly accelerate product delivery for a well-loved product with strong product-market fit.\n\n - Enjoy fully remote work with no “return to office” — we’ve been remote since day one.\n\n - Take advantage of flexible scheduling, a globally asynchronous team culture, and unlimited paid time off.\n\nOur Interview Process\n\nWe structure interviews around the real-world work you’ll do as a Platform Engineer:\n\n 1. Pre-screening assignment (Pull Request) followed by an initial interview.\n\n 2. Technical Design Document (TDD) assignment + review interview\n\n 3. Final hiring manager interview\n\nWe prioritize transparency and practical assessments over theoretical questions, ensuring our process aligns with your strengths and real-world experience.\n\nQuick Note on Scammers:\n\nClipboard would never ask you for money or your bank details to participate in our hiring process. Report any scammers impersonating the Clipboard hiring team members here https://forms.gle/SyGaxHFbon7Hg9fW6.",
